The paper presents a technique for multiclass and multilabel prediction, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the umbrella of several sub-categories in computer science. The use of stochastic gradient descent for training suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on efficient dynamic programming algorithms for inference suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The mention of multilabel datasets suggests that the paper may be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of logarithmic time and space suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
